<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 8. Gymnopus bulliformis. Caulocystidia from upper stipe. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 51955." , "Figure 6. Gymnopus bulliformis. Cheilocystidia. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 51955." , "Figure 3. Gymnopus bulliformis. Pileipellis elements. A Heterogeneous slime with secondarily septate hyphae B Secondary septa C, D Hyphae with gelatinized walls. Note clamp connections in D right. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 51955." , "Figure 1. Gymnopus bulliformis. A, B Basidiomata C, D Basidiospores. Standard bars: A, B = 20 mm; C, D = 5 µm. A, C WTU-F- 9305; B, D WTU-F- 51955." , "Figure 4. Gymnopus bulliformis. Pleurocystidia. Note acute apices and poorly-defined partitioned contents. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 51955." , "Figure 2. Gymnopus bulliformis. Pileal hairs. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 51955." , "Figure 5. Gymnopus bulliformis. Basidiole and basidia. Note long, awl-shaped sterigmata. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 51955." , "Figure 7. Gymnopus bulliformis. A Basidium B-G Cheilocystidia. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 9305." , "Figure 9. Gymnopus bulliformis. Caulocystidia from lower stipe. Standard bars = 10 µm. WTU-F- 51955." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115065" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115058" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115060" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115066" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115063" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115067" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115064" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115061" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/115062" .

